54749.name: Activate the Obelisk
54749.flavorText: A one-eyed, one stone, towering purple minion healer.

53408.name: Ancestral Guardian
53408.flavorText: No one knows whose ancestor he is, but he's still upset that you never call.

54772.name: Ancient Mysteries
54772.text: Draw a Secret from your deck. It costs (0).
54772.flavorText: I'm not saying it was aliens, but it was TOTALLY aliens!

54020.name: Anka, the Buried
54020.text: Battlecry: Change each Deathrattle minion in your hand into a 1/1 that costs (1).
54020.flavorText: "You look familiar. Were you at my first funeral?"

53615.name: Anubisath Defender
53615.text: Taunt. Costs (0) if you've cast a spell that costs (5) or more this turn.
53615.flavorText: Also comes running when he hears a can opener.

54257.name: Anubisath Warbringer
54257.text: Deathrattle: Give all minions in your hand +3/+3.
54257.flavorText: Some dogs will bring you a bone or a squeaky toy. This one brings war!

53822.name: Arcane Flakmage
53822.text: After you play a Secret, deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
53822.flavorText: Ancient pandaren proverb: He who is without secrets lacks flak.

53800.name: Armagedillo
53800.text: Taunt At the end of your turn, give all Taunt minions in your hand +2/+2.
53800.flavorText: We may never know what provoked it, but we will never forget the consequences.

54390.name: Armored Goon
54390.text: Whenever your hero attacks, gain 5 Armor.
54390.flavorText: Armored except for non-critical areas, such as the head, torso, fists and thighs.

53551.name: BEEEES!!!
53551.text: Choose a minion. Summon four 1/1 Bees that attack it.

54311.name: Bazaar Burglary
54311.text: Quest: Add 4 cards from other classes to your hand. Reward: Ancient Blades.
54311.flavorText: Just when you set up your "All-Natural Scented Candles" at the farmer's market and then some STUPID KOBOLD COMES AND TAKES THEM ALL!

54314.name: Bazaar Mugger
54314.text: Rush Battlecry: Add a random minion from another class to your hand.
54314.flavorText: Premium muggings at a discount price.

54269.name: Beaming Sidekick
54269.flavorText: Sure, I'll carry the water! And the food! And the tents! And the cursed monkey paw!

54296.name: Blatant Decoy
54296.text: Deathrattle: Each player summons the lowest Cost minion from their hand.
54296.flavorText: "Hah! You is being tricked by ME! Togwaggle!"

54492.name: Bloodsworn Mercenary
54492.text: Battlecry: Choose a damaged friendly minion. Summon a copy of it.
54492.flavorText: You look really hurt. You could use a friend!

54783.name: Body Wrapper
54783.text: Battlecry: Discover a friendly minion that died this game. Shuffle it into your deck.
54783.flavorText: She uses pickle slices for the eyes. Keeps them well-preserved.

54002.name: Bone Wraith
54002.flavorText: It uses only the eco-friendly bones from free-range humanoids.

53832.name: Brazen Zealot
53832.text: Whenever you summon a minion, gain +1 Attack.
53832.flavorText: Some paladins really Light it up.

54411.name: Bug Collector
54411.flavorText: The only one who likes BEEEES!!!

54317.name: Clever Disguise
54317.text: Add 2 random spells from another class to your hand.

54493.name: Cloud Prince
54493.text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, deal 6 damage.
54493.flavorText: "In West Cloudidelphia, born and raised; flinging lightning for the rest of my days."

54495.name: Colossus of the Moon
54495.flavorText: Strike him down, and you'll face the Colossus of the New Moon.

54280.name: Conjured Mirage
54280.text: Taunt At the start of your turn, shuffle this minion into your deck.

54369.name: Corrupt the Waters
54369.flavorText: This is why Hagatha is banned from public pools.

53545.name: Crystal Merchant
53545.text: If you have any unspent Mana at the end of your turn, draw a card.
53545.flavorText: I won't ask about your mana curve if you don't ask where I got these.

53890.name: Dark Pharaoh Tekahn
53890.text: Battlecry: For the rest of the game, your Lackeys are 4/4.
53890.flavorText: He'll get that League of Explorers and their little murloc too!

54488.name: Desert Hare
54488.flavorText: After they're caught, they’re dessert hares.

54288.name: Desert Obelisk
54288.text: If you control 3 of these at the end of your turn, deal 5 damage to a random enemy.
54288.flavorText: The Obelisk of the Stars can hide an entire land from prying eyes! Or zap a rando.

53860.name: Desert Spear
53860.text: After your hero attacks, summon a 1/1 Locust with Rush.
53860.flavorText: Goes on the right, next to the desert spoon.

53926.name: Dinotamer Brann
53926.text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, summon King Krush.
53926.flavorText: Brann's new dino-taming hobby is going well—his pet can already make him sit, stand, and roll over!

53889.name: Diseased Vulture
53889.text: Whenever your hero takes damage on your turn, summon a random 3-Cost minion.
53889.flavorText: He's off the twig! He's kicked the bucket! THIS IS AN EX-VULTURE!

54408.name: Dune Sculptor
54408.text: After you cast a spell, add a random Mage minion to your hand.
54408.flavorText: Come for the magic show, stay for the sand castles.

53343.name: Dwarven Archaeologist
53343.text: Battlecry: Discover a card. Reduce its Cost by (1).
53343.flavorText: She's making great progress on paying off that advanced degree.

53884.name: EVIL Recruiter
53884.text: Battlecry: Destroy a friendly Lackey to summon a 5/5 Demon.
53884.flavorText: I'm starting to think the lackeys aren't evil, just taken advantage of.

54009.name: EVIL Totem
54009.text: At the end of your turn, add a Lackey to your hand.
54009.flavorText: A lot of people blame the parents when a totem goes bad.

54160.name: Earthquake
54160.text: Deal 5 damage to all minions, then deal 2 damage to all minions.
54160.flavorText: Shake it, sh-sh-sh-shake it like a Kalimdor fissure.

53620.name: Elise the Enlightened
53620.text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, duplicate your hand.
53620.flavorText: From cartographer to combatant, Elise has taken the road less traveled—because no one else could find it on a map.

53932.name: Embalming Ritual
53932.flavorText: "Guess what! We're getting a new cat."

53885.name: Expired Merchant
53885.text: Battlecry: Discard your highest Cost card. Deathrattle: Add 2 copies of it to your hand.
53885.flavorText: The "best by" date is more like a guideline.

54191.name: Fishflinger
54191.text: Battlecry: Add a random Murloc to each player's hand.
54191.flavorText: The scent of fish lingers on the fishflinger's fish fingers.

53823.name: Flame Ward
53823.text: Secret: After a minion attacks your hero, deal 3 damage to all enemy minions.
53823.flavorText: Not to be confused with the burn ward.

54274.name: Frightened Flunky
54274.flavorText: Some people just aren't cut out to be supervillain material.

53613.name: Garden Gnome
53613.text: Battlecry: If you're holding a spell that costs (5) or more, summon two 2/2 Treants.
53613.flavorText: "Greetings, my little shrubs... It's whittlin' time."

53438.name: Generous Mummy
53438.flavorText: Yeah, she's mummified, but her money hasn’t dried up!

54264.name: Golden Scarab
54264.flavorText: Who actually puts all the gold plating on these things, and why?

54391.name: Hack the System
54391.text: Quest: Attack 5 times with your hero. Reward: Anraphet's Core.
54391.flavorText: Anything can be hacked, if you're holding an axe.

53576.name: Hidden Oasis
53576.text: Choose One - Summon a 6/6 Ancient with Taunt; or Restore 12 Health.
53576.flavorText: Amazing that it's been hidden, given the twenty-foot treant splashing around in it.

53929.name: High Priest Amet
53929.text: Whenever you summon a minion, set its Health equal to this minion's.
53929.flavorText: All minions are equal, but some minions are more equal than others.

54204.name: History Buff
54204.text: Whenever you play a minion, give a random minion in your hand +1/+1.

53971.name: Holy Ripple
53971.text: Deal 1 damage to all enemies. Restore 1 Health to all friendly characters.
53971.flavorText: I still prefer the taste of banana fudge ripple.

54015.name: Hooked Scimitar
54015.flavorText: Oooooooooooow. I'm hooked on a scimitar!

53861.name: Hunter's Pack
53861.text: Add a random Hunter Beast, Secret, and weapon to your hand.

53922.name: Hyena Alpha
53922.text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, summon two 2/2 Hyenas.
53922.flavorText: Everything the sun touches is ours—so long as it's already dead.

53938.name: Impbalming
53938.text: Destroy a minion. Shuffle 3 Worthless Imps into your deck.
53938.flavorText: With your complexion, Imp Balm is a great demonizer.

53788.name: Infested Goblin
53788.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Add two 1/1 Scarabs with Taunt to your hand.
53788.flavorText: Trust us. DON'T go cheap on the scarab repellent.

53796.name: Into the Fray
53796.text: Give all Taunt minions in your hand +2/+2.

54013.name: Jar Dealer
54013.text: Deathrattle: Add a random 1-Cost minion to your hand.
54013.flavorText: What's in the jar? It could be anyone!

53336.name: King Phaoris
53336.text: Battlecry: For each spell in your hand, summon a random minion of the same Cost.
53336.flavorText: When you're the king of the cats, the whole desert is your litterbox.

54259.name: Kobold Sandtrooper
54259.text: Deathrattle: Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero.

54389.name: Livewire Lance
54389.text: After your hero attacks, add a Lackey to your hand.
54389.flavorText: The lance is heavy but it’s the battery pack that really does a number on the shoulders.

54272.name: Living Monument
54272.flavorText: This is not the greatest card in the world. This is just a monument.

53907.name: Making Mummies
53907.flavorText: "I do say, this gives me the vapors every single time!"

53445.name: Micro Mummy
53445.text: Reborn At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Attack.
53445.flavorText: The dramatically detailed terrifically trimmed replica of the real thing!

53582.name: Mischief Maker
53582.text: Battlecry: Swap the top card of your deck with your opponent's.
53582.flavorText: Fair trade is for noble-minded suckers with dignity and honor.

54291.name: Mogu Cultist
54291.text: Battlecry: If your board is full of Mogu Cultists, sacrifice them all and summon Highkeeper Ra.
54291.flavorText: Mogu cultists have the worst team-building exercises.

53972.name: Mogu Fleshshaper
53972.text: Rush. Costs (1) less for each minion on the battlefield.
53972.flavorText: He's here to shape *clap* you up!

54284.name: Mortuary Machine
54284.text: After your opponent plays a minion, give it Reborn.
54284.flavorText: The ankle bone's connected to the shin bone. The knuckle bone's connected to the... eh, it'll be fine.

54730.name: Murmy
54730.flavorText: Unlike other mummies, they rolled him up with rice, sliced cucumbers, and soy sauce on the side.

53974.name: Naga Sand Witch
53974.text: Battlecry: Change the Cost of spells in your hand to (5).

54276.name: Neferset Ritualist
54276.text: Battlecry: Restore adjacent minions to full Health.
54276.flavorText: The Neferset are great—they'll always make sure their friends are feline fine.

53883.name: Neferset Thrasher
53883.text: Whenever this attacks, deal 3 damage to your hero.
53883.flavorText: Tough to do skateboard tricks with four legs.

54489.name: Oasis Surger
54489.text: Rush Choose One - Gain +2/+2; or Summon a copy of this minion.

54147.name: Octosari
54147.flavorText: Eight arms of sand-flinging, foe-wringing, card-slinging fury!

53979.name: Overflow
53979.text: Restore 5 Health to all characters. Draw 5 cards.
53979.flavorText: It's a high five followed by a low tide.

54425.name: Penance
54425.flavorText: This is what happens when you don’t give a sincere apology.

54153.name: Phalanx Commander
54153.flavorText: Turns out he's really good at herding cats.

54261.name: Pharaoh Cat
54261.text: Battlecry: Add a random Reborn minion to your hand.
54261.flavorText: Mightiest of mousers, enduring in kingship of the upper and lower cat tree, conqueror of the red dot, the all-wise Catshepsut.

53827.name: Pharaoh's Blessing
53827.flavorText: Life hack: Sneeze near a pharaoh.

54431.name: Plague of Death
54431.flavorText: Don't worry, there's a happy little funhouse right under that sand pit.

54429.name: Plague of Flames
54429.text: Destroy all your minions. For each one, destroy a random enemy minion.

54426.name: Plague of Madness
54426.text: Each player equips a 2/2 Knife with Poisonous.
54426.flavorText: Don't bring a candle to a knife fight.

53985.name: Plague of Murlocs
53985.text: Transform all minions into random Murlocs.

53919.name: Pressure Plate
53919.text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, destroy a random enemy minion.
53919.flavorText: The appropriate dishware for stressful situations.

53935.name: Psychopomp
53935.text: Battlecry: Summon a random friendly minion that died this game. Give it Reborn.
53935.flavorText: "Come with me if you want to re-live."

53947.name: Questing Explorer
53947.text: Battlecry: If you control a Quest, draw a card.
53947.flavorText: Earned her merit badges the hard way—twelve zhevra hooves at a time.

54278.name: Quicksand Elemental
54278.text: Battlecry: Give all enemy minions -2 Attack this turn.
54278.flavorText: Use a light abrasive to buff blemishes away but use a heavy abrasive to debuff problems.

53945.name: Raid the Sky Temple
53945.flavorText: "Why can't I hold all these scrolls?"

53917.name: Ramkahen Wildtamer
53917.text: Battlecry: Copy a random Beast in your hand.
53917.flavorText: She gets to decide what cards go to the Hall of Fame.

53778.name: Reno the Relicologist
53778.text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemy minions.
53778.flavorText: All his life, Reno Jackson was only a gatling wand away from becoming the greatest and most terrifying mage who ever existed.

53887.name: Riftcleaver
53887.text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion. Your hero takes damage equal to its Health.
53887.flavorText: Brings you face to face with your destructive impulses.

54011.name: Sahket Sapper
54011.text: Deathrattle: Return a random enemy minion to your opponent's hand.

54037.name: Salhet's Pride
54037.text: Deathrattle: Draw two 1-Health minions from your deck.

53969.name: Sandhoof Waterbearer
53969.text: At the end of your turn, restore 5 Health to a damaged friendly character.
53969.flavorText: Used to carrying for his team.

53967.name: Sandstorm Elemental
53967.text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. Overload: (1)
53967.flavorText: Doot doot doot doot doot [Pause] Doot doot doot doot doot DEE doot doot doot doot doot!

54038.name: Sandwasp Queen
54038.text: Battlecry: Add two 2/1 Sandwasps to your hand.
54038.flavorText: Oooh, see that wasp! Watch that sting! Dig in the Sandwasp Queen!

53609.name: Scarlet Webweaver
53609.text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of a random Beast in your hand by (5).
53609.flavorText: Isn't that nice? The spider made the explorer a sleeping bag!

54077.name: Serpent Egg
54077.flavorText: These things go from "adorable danger noodle!" to "MY FACE IS MELTING!" all too quickly.

54016.name: Shadow of Death
54016.text: Choose a minion. Shuffle 3 'Shadows' into your deck that summon a copy when drawn.

53882.name: Sinister Deal
53882.flavorText: "So, what's in the sack?" "Something... sinister." "Okay, it's a deal."

53379.name: Sir Finley of the Sands
53379.text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, Discover an upgraded Hero Power.
53379.flavorText: "The sands shall be my sea! And this scarab shall be my, er, strange and wriggly boat!"

54256.name: Spitting Camel
54256.text: At the end of your turn, deal 1 damage to another random friendly minion.
54256.flavorText: Were you expectorating another bad pun?

53661.name: Splitting Axe
53661.flavorText: The ancient shaman chant, "Control Axe, Control Vee."

54806.name: Subdue
54806.text: Set a minion's Attack and Health to 1.

54154.name: Sunstruck Henchman
54154.text: At the start of your turn, this has a 50% chance to fall asleep.
54154.flavorText: There is E.V.I.L. here that DOES sleep.

53739.name: Supreme Archaeology
53739.flavorText: Archaeology is the discovery of rare and powerful artifacts. Supreme Archaeology is TAKING THEM!

54424.name: Swarm of Locusts
54424.flavorText: Good things never come in swarms.

54260.name: Temple Berserker
54260.flavorText: He's back. He's angry. And he's here to wrap things up.

54427.name: Tip the Scales
54427.flavorText: Hold on, I need to get some murlocs to weigh in on this.

53791.name: Tomb Warden
53791.text: Taunt Battlecry: Summon a copy of this minion.
53791.flavorText: Also known as an ancient copy machine.

53771.name: Tortollan Pilgrim
53771.text: Battlecry: Discover a spell in your deck and cast it with random targets.
53771.flavorText: A tortollan made it to the desert!

53978.name: Totemic Surge
53978.flavorText: It's not really advanced shamanic magic, you just draw nasty eyebrows on them.

53496.name: Untapped Potential
53496.text: Quest: End 4 turns with any unspent Mana. Reward: Ossirian Tear.

53990.name: Vessina
53990.text: While you're Overloaded, your other minions have +2 Attack.
53990.flavorText: She wasn't happy when Hagatha sent her back to Uldum. But her "angry" hiss sounds like her "happy" hiss, so no one knew the difference.

54433.name: Vilefiend
54433.flavorText: Dreamed of becoming a Stylefiend, but fel was never in season.

53413.name: Vulpera Scoundrel
53413.text: Battlecry: Discover a spell or pick a mystery choice.
53413.flavorText: A spell is a spell, but the mystery choice could be anything! (It's also a spell.)

54000.name: Wasteland Assassin
54000.flavorText: They'll never see me coming, what with my glowing body, eyes and daggers.

54273.name: Wasteland Scorpid
54273.flavorText: After they get to a certain size, it doesn't matter if they're poisonous or not.

53973.name: Weaponized Wasp
53973.text: Battlecry: If you control a Lackey, deal 3 damage.
53973.flavorText: Dr. Boom had one simple request: wasps with flippin' laser beams attached to their heads.

53627.name: Whirlkick Master
53627.text: Whenever you play a Combo card, add a random Combo card to your hand.

53435.name: Wild Bloodstinger
53435.text: Battlecry: Summon a minion from your opponent's hand. Attack it.
53435.flavorText: Tame Bloodstingers would politely invite your minion to tea.

53596.name: Worthy Expedition
53596.flavorText: This isn't where I parked my mount.

53439.name: Wrapped Golem
53439.text: Reborn At the end of your turn, summon a 1/1 Scarab with Taunt.
53439.flavorText: The end result of one of the greatest wrap battles of all time.

53942.name: Wretched Reclaimer
53942.text: Battlecry: Destroy a friendly minion, then return it to life with full Health.
53942.flavorText: "Ok, here's the plan. We kill you, then bring you back." "Stronger?" "No, about the same."

53756.name: Zephrys the Great
53756.text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, wish for the perfect card.
53756.flavorText: "Of course it's perfect, you're just not seeing how to use it."
